This paper deals with coreference phenomena in neural machine translation systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and machine learning algorithms, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the machine translation systems, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper compares the features of coreference chains in machine translated outputs to those of the source texts and human translations, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
